<title>UK: Lintas wins ad campaign for Hungary's RTL Klub TV.</title>
<headline>Lintas wins ad campaign for Hungary's RTL Klub TV.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-07-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ammirati Puris Lintas Budapest on Tuesday said it has been awarded the advertising launch campaign of RTL Klub, the new Hungarian commercial television channel owned by telecommunications consortium Magyar RTL.</p>
<p>Lintas, owned by Interpublic Group of Cos Inc, said it won the account after a two-round pitch involving five other Hungarian agencies.</p>
<p>Lintas released a statement in London announcing the account win.</p>
<p>The Magyar RTL consortium includes European broadcasting group CLT-UFA, Britain's Pearson Plc and Hungarian telecom group Matav. It successfully bid for a 10-year commercial television licence earlier this month and under the terms of the franchise must start broadcasting by October 7.</p>
<p>-- London Advertising Newsdesk +44 171 542 4770 ($ = 195.8 Hungarian Forints)</p>
